# ESLint config (`**/eslint.config.*`)

## Stack alignment
- Keep **Next.js**, **React**, **TypeScript**, and **Tailwind** plugins at versions compatible with **ESLint** flat config used in the repo.

## Tailwind
- **`eslint-plugin-tailwindcss`** (or equivalent): class order rules should match **Prettier** / team habits—avoid noisy autofixes that fight formatter unless CI requires them.

## CI
- **`npm run lint`** / **`eslint .`** in CI should use the **same** config as local—no hidden `.eslintrc` unless migration is documented.

## Scope
- Do not disable **a11y** or **react-hooks** rules globally without team approval; prefer narrow **`eslint-disable-next-line`** at call sites with comments.
